HEADWORD: Consulate
<hw>Con"su*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>consulatus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>consulat</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The office of a consul.</def> <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The jurisdiction or residence of a consul.</def>
<rj><au>Kent.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Consular government; term of office of a
consul.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Consulship</ent>⟦br⟧
